WEBVTT

00:04.908 --> 00:07.276
Moira: John! Are you awake?

00:07.311 --> 00:09.846
- John!
- What? What's happening?

00:09.880 --> 00:12.664
Your wayfaring thespian has returned!

00:13.025 --> 00:15.394
I-I don't wanna jinx anything,

00:15.419 --> 00:17.720
but the shoot was a triumph.

00:17.755 --> 00:20.456
The local Bosnians are calling
it a stunning re-invigoration

00:20.491 --> 00:22.558
of the "Crows Have Eyes" franchise.

00:22.757 --> 00:24.594
That, of course, is a loose translation.

00:24.628 --> 00:26.929
Oh, well that sounds
great, sweetheart.

00:26.964 --> 00:29.632
John, no need to
get out of bed, dear.

00:29.666 --> 00:32.502
I'm sure you considered
planning a little more fanfare

00:32.527 --> 00:34.194
for my return, but...

00:34.238 --> 00:36.639
oh, it's best to ease back in.

00:36.673 --> 00:38.207
It's 3:30 in the morning,

00:38.234 --> 00:41.236
you said you were
coming in today at noon.

00:41.278 --> 00:44.247
Yes! Noon Bosnian
Mountain Time, that is!

00:44.281 --> 00:46.482
Which was several hours ago, John.

00:46.517 --> 00:48.985
Oh, and what a journey it has been!

00:49.019 --> 00:50.887
Production had me routed through Nairobi

00:50.921 --> 00:53.189
for some reason, and then
our plane was grounded

00:53.223 --> 00:55.758
after flying through a swarm of locusts.

00:55.793 --> 00:57.660
I didn't want to miss
my third connection,

00:57.694 --> 01:00.696
so I took a Bosnian
upper just to keep awake.

01:00.731 --> 01:02.242
Those things are the size of a nickel,

01:02.266 --> 01:03.866
so I only took one,

01:03.901 --> 01:05.101
at least, I think I did.

01:05.135 --> 01:06.913
I may have taken a second
one just to be safe,

01:06.937 --> 01:10.106
because I don't know if I
took that first one, or not.

01:10.140 --> 01:12.875
Either way, I've been up
since eight am three days ago,

01:12.910 --> 01:14.277
with time changes factored in,

01:14.311 --> 01:16.379
and I couldn't be happier to see you!

01:16.413 --> 01:17.680
Oh!

01:17.714 --> 01:20.917
Well Moira, it sounds
like a nightmare of a trip.

01:20.951 --> 01:22.919
Why don't we leave the
unpacking 'til tomorrow,

01:22.953 --> 01:25.221
and just get some rest?

01:25.255 --> 01:26.486
Good idea.

01:27.591 --> 01:28.658
Kids!

01:28.692 --> 01:30.660
- No Moira, it's 3:30.
- David!

01:30.694 --> 01:32.261
Alexis!

01:33.363 --> 01:35.131
- Oh! Who is it?
- Oh my God, what?!

01:35.165 --> 01:38.501
I don't know what you kids
are still doing up so late.

01:38.535 --> 01:40.169
I didn't want to disturb you,

01:40.204 --> 01:43.039
I just wanted you to know that
Mummy got home safe and sound!

01:43.073 --> 01:44.273
- Okay, good night.
- Great.

01:44.308 --> 01:46.175
Okay, if you insist, one quick story.

01:46.210 --> 01:48.744
So, day three of shooting, Hamza and I

01:48.779 --> 01:51.347
find ourselves stuck in a hail storm...

01:51.381 --> 01:52.792
Oh my God, not tonight,
thank you, though.

01:52.816 --> 01:55.651
I'm sorry kids, your mother's
had a rough couple of days.

01:55.686 --> 01:58.154
Moira, why don't we
get to bed, sweetheart?

01:58.188 --> 01:59.956
Ooh, frisky, John.

01:59.990 --> 02:02.458
- Oh! Bye!
- Ewww!

02:02.493 --> 02:05.194
- Eww.
- Ugh!

02:05.229 --> 02:09.764
Subtitle sync and corrections by
<font color="#FF0000"><b>ChrisKe</b></font> for <font color="#FF0000"><b>www.addic7ed.com.</b></font>

02:10.808 --> 02:13.910
Moira: No! No one would believe this!

02:14.124 --> 02:15.992
These cannot be real!

02:16.831 --> 02:18.521
What's going on?

02:18.976 --> 02:20.743
Well, instead of sleeping last night,

02:20.777 --> 02:22.678
I decided to just power right through.

02:22.713 --> 02:24.647
You know, best to round
up to an even four days.

02:24.681 --> 02:27.517
And while I was doing
some light reorganization,

02:27.551 --> 02:30.553
I came upon this stack of love letters

02:30.587 --> 02:33.210
written to your father by another woman.

02:33.690 --> 02:37.293
- Okay.
- Best not to be concerned, Alexis.

02:37.327 --> 02:40.763
I'm sure there's a logical
explanation for all of this.

02:40.797 --> 02:43.232
- Sure there is.
- Yes. Some of them!

02:43.267 --> 02:45.067
Some of them are even funny!

02:45.102 --> 02:47.904
Listen. Where's that one? Oh! Read this.

02:53.110 --> 02:55.344
"Dearest John-John,

02:55.379 --> 02:57.613
I'm lying here, stuck, sweaty.

02:57.648 --> 02:59.615
All I can think about is you,

02:59.650 --> 03:01.183
and the last night we spent together,

03:01.225 --> 03:02.725
bed shaking... " Ew!

03:02.750 --> 03:04.083
Why are you making me read this?

03:04.121 --> 03:05.788
- I know, right?
- Eugh!

03:05.822 --> 03:07.423
Before your father met me,

03:07.457 --> 03:09.091
he was not quite so selective.

03:09.126 --> 03:11.727
I hesitate to add, he
even had a predilection

03:11.762 --> 03:13.863
for boom boom girls!

03:14.153 --> 03:15.464
Okay, I would like to remind you

03:15.499 --> 03:17.433
that I don't have a therapist anymore.

03:17.467 --> 03:18.968
No, as you said,

03:19.002 --> 03:21.337
there's a logical
explanation for all of this.

03:21.371 --> 03:24.373
No, you've said that
like, three times now.

03:24.408 --> 03:26.208
So I think it's probably for the best

03:26.243 --> 03:28.932
that we put these down,
and we go have a nap, okay?

03:28.957 --> 03:30.746
- Yes. You're right.
- Mhm.

03:30.781 --> 03:33.316
You're right, Alexis,
you're always so right.

03:35.352 --> 03:37.219
Okay.

03:37.254 --> 03:40.189
All right...

03:43.060 --> 03:46.062
Just a few more, just
to lull me to sleep.

03:46.096 --> 03:47.286
That's all.

